(Atomic Guava - Peasants of the future - 2022)

Through weather and storms and the pull of the waves
The words of my father and figure remain
Etched in my palm as the tears filled his eyes
I'll be your strong shoulder as long as you’re mine

My heart hangs heavy and low
Sheltered myself in a fruit that explodes
Like the anger bottled inside of my chest
Until the end, my friends, anchors away

